# Add Redis Streams to Book Management System

This plan adds 2 Redis Streams features to the existing FastAPI project using **only new files**.  
The only change to an existing file is adding 2 router imports in [main.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/Redis_project/main.py).

---

## Proposed Changes

### Feature 1 — Activity Event Stream (`audit_stream`)

Every meaningful action in the system (borrow, return, review, rate…) is published to a Redis Stream `audit_stream` via `XADD`. The stream can then be queried or consumed by any interested service.

#### [NEW] [stream_repository.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/Redis_project/repositories/stream_repository.py)
Low-level Redis Streams wrappers:
- `publish(stream, fields)` → `XADD stream * field value …`
- `read_range(stream, start, end, count)` → `XRANGE`
- `read_latest(stream, count)` → `XREVRANGE`
- `create_consumer_group(stream, group, start_id)` → `XGROUP CREATE`
- `read_group(stream, group, consumer, count)` → `XREADGROUP`
- `ack(stream, group, *ids)` → `XACK`

#### [NEW] [stream_service.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/Redis_project/services/stream_service.py)
High-level helpers that call `StreamRepository`:
- `publish_event(action, description, book_id, user_id)` — XADD with timestamp
- `get_all_events(count)` — XREVRANGE last N events
- `get_events_by_book(book_id, count)` — filter from XRANGE result

#### [NEW] [stream_routes.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/Redis_project/routes/stream_routes.py)
REST endpoints (prefix `/stream`, admin-only):
- `GET /stream/events?count=50` — last N events from the stream
- `GET /stream/events/{book_id}?count=50` — events filtered by book

---

### Feature 2 — Overdue Borrow Detection Stream (`overdue_stream`)

A **producer** scans all active borrows and publishes overdue ones to `overdue_stream` via `XADD`.  
A **consumer group** (`overdue_processors`) reads and processes those events, marking each borrow hash with `status = overdue` in Redis.

#### [NEW] [overdue_producer.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/Redis_project/services/overdue_producer.py)
- `scan_and_publish()` — reads all borrow hashes from [BorrowRepository](file:///c:/Users/HP/Redis_project/repositories/borrow_repository.py#7-47), compares `due_date` to today, `XADD`s an event for each overdue book with fields: `book_id`, `user_id`, `due_date`, `days_overdue`

#### [NEW] [overdue_consumer.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/Redis_project/services/overdue_consumer.py)
- `process_overdue_events()` — creates consumer group lazily, `XREADGROUP` reads pending events, sets `hset borrow:{book_id} status overdue`, then `XACK`s processed messages

#### [NEW] [overdue_routes.py](file:///c:/Users/HP/Redis_project/routes/overdue_routes.py)
REST endpoints (prefix `/overdue`):
- `POST /overdue/scan` *(admin-only)* — triggers `scan_and_publish()` + `process_overdue_events()`
- `GET /overdue/list` *(admin-only)* — lists all borrows with `status = overdue`

